in larchmont.

07:45.630 --> 07:47.985
They want us to assess.
Jack, let's go.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.822
You're tailing.

07:56.240 --> 07:57.492
I'm ron.
I live next door.

07:57.510 --> 07:59.501
I was out walking
cheeky here when, bam,

07:59.510 --> 08:00.705
Hannah ran
right into me,

08:00.710 --> 08:02.804
Probably scared me more
than I scared her.

08:02.810 --> 08:04.869
Janice: And none of you
saw or heard anything

08:04.880 --> 08:06.041
Out of the ordinary
last night?

08:06.050 --> 08:07.848
Woman: Just hannah screaming.
I live across the street.

08:07.850 --> 08:10.273
I was watching letterman,
and I called the police.

08:10.290 --> 08:12.782
Different woman: I live
right around the corner,

08:12.790 --> 08:16.055
Out like a light.
Sorry.

08:16.060 --> 08:18.779
Hannah: And then we ran
out of the house and into ron.

08:18.790 --> 08:20.485
He called 911,
and that was it.

08:20.500 --> 08:21.899
Ron is your
neighbor?

08:21.900 --> 08:24.870
Yeah. He was out
walking his dog.

08:24.870 --> 08:26.122
By the time
the cops came,

08:26.130 --> 08:27.359
Whoever it was
was gone.

08:27.370 --> 08:29.236
Is anything missing
in the house?

08:29.240 --> 08:31.038
No, not that my mom
and I could tell.

08:31.040 --> 08:35.409
In your statement, it says you
believe someone is following you.

08:35.409 --> 08:39.539
Every once in a while, I feel
like someone is watching me.

08:39.549 --> 08:41.871
I'll turn around, but
then no one is there,

08:41.880 --> 08:44.315
And it's really
freaky, you know?

08:44.320 --> 08:45.515
Mm-hmm.

08:45.520 --> 08:48.285
I can feel it,
and then somebody

08:48.290 --> 08:50.759
The last couple of weeks
has been in the back yard.

08:50.760 --> 08:53.252
They've been wearing
a hoodie or something.

08:53.260 --> 08:54.955
Hannah, why didn't
you tell your mom?

08:54.960 --> 08:57.429
She works a lot, and I
didn't want to worry her.

08:57.430 --> 09:00.195
Besides, who's
gonna believe me?

09:00.200 --> 09:02.862
I mean, it's not like I
have proof or anything.

09:02.870 --> 09:05.407
I believe you, hannah.
All right.

09:05.410 --> 09:07.139
Here's what I want
you to do.

09:07.140 --> 09:09.677
I want you to write down
every time you remember

09:09.680 --> 09:11.546
Someone watching you--
what day it was,

09:11.550 --> 09:13.302
What time it was,
anything that can help us

09:13.320 --> 09:15.277
Identify your
stalker's patterns.

09:15.280 --> 09:16.918
But I've never even
seen his face.

09:16.920 --> 09:18.888
I know, but your instincts
become my clues.

09:18.890 --> 09:20.415
A timeline will
really help us.

09:20.420 --> 09:23.720
Stalking usually begins
with a benign crush

09:23.730 --> 09:25.255
Or a fixation,
and it escalates

09:25.260 --> 09:27.251
Into something that
becomes more frequent.

09:27.260 --> 09:30.628
As the obsession grows,
so does the stalker's courage

09:30.630 --> 09:34.396
And his need
to reach out.

09:34.400 --> 09:37.665
Hannah, don't worry,
all right?

09:37.670 --> 09:40.207
We're gonna find out
who's doing this.

09:40.210 --> 09:42.099
<i>Woman: It's just
the two kids.</i>

