All my friends do.

33:25.000 --> 33:29.528
Which house did you
say you lived in?

33:29.540 --> 33:34.467
Just across,
two doors down.

33:36.710 --> 33:40.408
Is it sugar that
you said you wanted?

33:40.410 --> 33:43.209
Yeah, just a cup.

33:43.220 --> 33:46.747
The recipe
requires two.

33:48.890 --> 33:51.757
Thomas, run.
No!

33:51.760 --> 33:58.257
James, baby! James!
James, where are you?

33:59.400 --> 34:01.129
Baby!

34:01.140 --> 34:03.734
[pounding on door]

34:03.740 --> 34:05.060
James!

34:05.070 --> 34:09.974
I'm not your son.
Go away.

34:09.980 --> 34:11.469
[crash]

34:11.480 --> 34:14.677
[pounding stops]

34:21.219 --> 34:26.420
Thomas?
Thomas, it's the police.

34:28.159 --> 34:31.289
Where's judith?

34:33.929 --> 34:37.230
Thomas, unlock the door.

34:37.239 --> 34:38.833
I don't know you.

34:38.840 --> 34:40.239
Yeah, you do.
We met at your house.

34:40.239 --> 34:42.436
I'm gonna take you
to your mom's.

34:42.440 --> 34:46.172
Open the door, buddy.

34:52.550 --> 34:56.043
You ruined
my life, james.

34:56.060 --> 34:59.086
Drop it! Now!

34:59.090 --> 35:01.229
Beth: It's ok.
It's ok.

35:01.230 --> 35:05.656
It's all right.
Everything is ok, jack.

35:07.770 --> 35:12.867
Judy, it's me,
your friend.

35:12.870 --> 35:16.738
You don't want to hurt james.
You love him, remember?

35:16.740 --> 35:21.246
Judith, don't do this.
This is thomas mccoy.

35:21.250 --> 35:24.777
It's not james.
Thomas is not james.

35:24.790 --> 35:26.849
Oh...

35:26.850 --> 35:28.545
James is gone.

35:28.560 --> 35:30.585
Judy?
No.

35:30.590 --> 35:34.686
Yes. Yes.

35:34.700 --> 35:36.555
Oh...

35:36.560 --> 35:40.064
[sobbing]

35:42.340 --> 35:43.830
Uh!

35:43.840 --> 35:47.162
Oh...

35:47.170 --> 35:48.660
You can trust me.

35:48.680 --> 35:51.706
I'm gonna get you the
help you need, all right?

35:51.710 --> 35:53.576
It hurts.

35:53.580 --> 35:57.312
It won't stop
hurting.

35:58.320 --> 36:00.846
[sobbing]

36:06.560 --> 36:09.120
[music playing]

36:15.770 --> 36:18.831
[distant siren]

36:22.040 --> 36:26.500
[police radio chatter]

36:32.890 --> 36:35.712
[no dialogue]

37:23.340 --> 37:25.729
I like you.

37:25.740 --> 37:26.935
What?

37:26.940 --> 37:29.136
I don't care if you
don't like me.

37:29.140 --> 37:30.539
I like you.

37:30.540 --> 37:33.180
You are one
awkward dude.

37:33.180 --> 37:35.569
Hmm.

37:40.550 --> 37:42.746
Hey.
Hey.

37:42.760 --> 37:44.717
Want to grab a drink
and bond some?

37:44.730 --> 37:47.381
Strictly platonic,
for the most part.

37:47.390 --> 37:50.519
Is it ever platonic?

37:53.100 --> 37:55.990
If I go to drinks with you and
get even the slightest bit buzzed,

37:56.000 --> 37:58.970
I'm gonna turn into that guy
because you are a really hot woman.

37:58.970 --> 38:01.359
So please don't
take this the wrong way.

38:01.380 --> 38:03.200
I've been that guy.

38:03.210 --> 38:06.430
I don't want to be that guy,
not here at work with you.

38:06.450 --> 38:09.408
I'd like to keep
things clean.

38:09.420 --> 38:11.912
You mind if we don't?

38:11.920 --> 38:15.242
It was just
drinks, jack.

38:15.260 --> 38:20.380
It's never just
drinks, janice.

38:26.000 --> 38:30.790
Wow, did he
just reject you?

38:30.800 --> 38:32.495
That's got to hurt.

38:32.510 --> 38:33.568
On the contrary.

38:33.570 --> 38:38.804
He just got
more interesting.

38:55.660 --> 38:58.925
We never got a chance to
finish our conversation.

38:58.930 --> 39:02.423
So let's finish it. Go.

39:02.440 --> 39:04.363
I know I hurt you.

39:04.370 --> 39:05.838
I know you'll
never forgive me.

39:05.840 --> 39:08.366
I wouldn't even
ask you to,

39:08.380 --> 39:12.908
But I'm not here to ruin
your life, either.

39:12.910 --> 39:14.844
I just--

39:16.350 --> 39:18.546
I just want the chance
to know my son.

39:18.550 --> 39:21.520
I don't want you
to know him, jack.

39:21.520 --> 39:25.013
You're not worthy of him.
Do you understand that?

39:25.030 --> 39:26.828
I would never hurt him.

39:26.830 --> 39:28.753
Famous last words,
jack.

39:28.760 --> 39:31.229
Now it's my turn,
so listen up.

39:31.230 --> 39:33.619
You have two weeks
to get out of |.A.

39:33.630 --> 39:36.167
Put in for a transfer.
Quit. Go back to new york.

39:36.170 --> 39:38.696
I don't care,
but if you do not leave,

39:38.710 --> 39:40.804
I will go to beth
and your division captain

39:40.810 --> 39:42.300
And I will tell them
that little thing

39:42.310 --> 39:44.278
That I know
and nobody else does,

39:44.280 --> 39:46.305
And it will ruin you.

39:46.310 --> 39:48.540
Now, I know you care
about your career.

39:48.550 --> 39:50.678
In fact, it's the only
thing that you care about.

39:50.680 --> 39:57.689
So don't be stupid.
I repeat, two weeks.

39:58.260 --> 40:01.025
[music playing]

40:19.550 --> 40:21.348
[keys clatter]

40:21.350 --> 40:26.049
[beep beep]

41:12.700 --> 41:15.123
Perry: Can I get
a manhattan?

41:15.140 --> 41:19.839
You look pretty young.
Can I see some 1.D.?

41:19.840 --> 41:22.707
[laughs]

41:26.250 --> 41:30.414
You got something
against younger men? Yes...

41:32.620 --> 41:34.679
And no.

41:42.430 --> 41:44.421
One manhattan
coming up.
